quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  29,39,"[In the case of] Qarun, Pharaoh and Haman, Moses brought them explanations and they [still] acted overbearing on earth; yet they could never get ahead [of Us]."
  29,40,"Each We seized for his offence; some of them We sent a hailstorm against, some the Blast overtook, others of them We let the earth swallow up, while still others We drowned. It was not Allah (God) Who wronged them, but they had already wronged themselves."
  29,41,"Those who enlist other patrons instead of Allah (God) may be compared to the Spider, who adopts a house for himself. The flimsiest house is the Spider's house, if they only realized it!"
  29,42,"Allah (God) knows anything they may appeal to besides Himself; He is the Powerful, the Wise."
  29,43,"These are parables We make up for mankind, though only the learned will use their [powers of] reason."
  29,44,"Allah (God) created Heaven and Earth in [all] Truth; in that is a sign for believers!"
  29,45,"Recite whatever has been revealed to you from the Book (the Quran), and keep up prayer: prayer restrains one from sexual misconduct and debauchery. Yet mentioning Allah (God) is even more important, for Allah (God) knows whatever you produce."